# Frontend standards

The frontend is a Next.js 14 App Router app under `frontend/src/`, using the
`@/` alias (maps to `frontend/src/`).

## File placement

| Kind | Location | Import from |
|------|----------|-------------|
| Routes, layout, page, global CSS | `app/` | — |
| React components | `components/` (flat) | `@/components/...` |
| API client, hooks, helpers, config | `lib/` | `@/lib/...` |
| `interface` shapes | `interfaces/*.ts` | `@/interfaces` |

`interfaces/` is barrel-exported via `interfaces/index.ts`; add new public
interfaces there. Other folders are imported by file path.

## Interfaces & types

- Do not define `interface` shapes inside `components/` or `app/`.
- Domain interfaces → `interfaces/domain.interface.ts`; API envelope/types →
  `interfaces/api.interface.ts`; component props →
  `interfaces/component-props.interface.ts`.

## Data fetching

- All HTTP goes through the helpers in `lib/api.ts`, which use the native
  `fetch`, unwrap the backend `{ status, entity }` envelope (`handle`), and
  resolve the base URL via `lib/config.ts` (`API_URL` in the browser,
  `INTERNAL_API_URL` for server-side requests).
- Write requests (upload) send the shared secret via the `x-api-key` header.
  There is no bearer/JWT auth.
- SSE uses the native `EventSource` via the `useArtifactEvents` hook in `lib/`;
  no token is attached.

## Styling

- Global CSS with CSS variables in `app/globals.css`. No Tailwind or CSS-in-JS.

## Verification

```bash
cd frontend && npm run build   # next build (also type-checks)
cd frontend && npm run lint    # next lint
```
